nt\": \"productcatalogservice-1\",\n      \"reason\": \"Significant spike in both 'request' and 'response' times, indicating possible processing bottleneck or task overload.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"request median increased from 84.0 to 11337.5; response median increased from 72.0 to 9635.0.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend-1\",\n      \"reason\": \"Increased 'server_error_ratio' and 'error_ratio', suggesting heightened server-side errors during the anomaly.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"server_error_ratio p99 swelled from 0.18 to 2.63.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"shippingservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Detected substantial client error ratios, hinting at service instability or improper client handling.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"client_error_ratio p99 reached 38.0.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Summary\nThere are clear indicators of service instability, particularly in Product Catalog and Frontend services, coupled with observable strain on Shipping services due to errors. The changes in the node's memory performance on `aiops-k8s-08` suggest external pressure rather than an intrinsic fault of the node. Further investigation on application-level resource management and error handling might be required for mitigation."}
